<FIRST>u a AM-TechnicalEmmys     09-17 0877</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Technical Emmys,0937</SECOND>
<HEAD>`Lonesome Dove' Dominates Technical Emmys</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PASADENA, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The popular CBS miniseries ``Lonesome
Dove'' stampeded over the competition Saturday night with six Emmy
awards in the technical categories announced by the Television
Academy.
   Thirteen other shows won two technical awards each, including the
CBS fantasy ``Beauty and the Beast,'' ABC's ``thirtysomething'' and
the Fox Network's ``The Tracey Ullman Show.''
   CBS, which has been a ratings loser, led the technical awards
race with 21, followed by NBC with 13. ABC and the Public
Broadcasting System received seven program and individual awards
each. The Fox Network and the syndicated show ``Star Trek: The Next
Generation'' won two awards each. Home Box Office and the Turner
Broadcasting System each won one award.
   Awards in the major Emmy categories will be presented Sunday
night at the Pasadena Civic Auditorium in a three-hour-plus ceremony
to be broadcast live by Fox Broadcasting at 8 p.m. EDT.
   Here is a complete list of winners in technical categories of the
41st annual Prime Time Emmy Awards, with multiple awards given in
some categories:
   1. ART DIRECTION, SERIES: ``Moonlighting: A Womb with a View,''
ABC.
   2. ART DIRECTION, VARIETY OR MUSIC PROGRAM: ``The Tracey Ullman
Show,'' Fox.
   3. ART DIRECTION, MINISERIES OR SPECIAL: ``I'll Be Home for
Christmas,'' NBC.
   4. CHOREOGRAPHY: ``Disney-MGM Studios Theme Park Grand Opening,''
NBC; ``The Tracey Ullman Show,'' Fox.
   5. CINEMATOGRAPHY, SERIES: ``Quantum Leap: Pilot,'' NBC.
   6. CINEMATOGRAPHY, MINISERIES OR SPECIAL: ``Shooter,'' NBC.
   7. COSTUMING, SERIES: ``thirtysomething: We'll Meet Again,'' ABC.
   8. COSTUME DESIGN, SERIES: ``Beauty and the Beast: The
Outsiders,'' CBS.
   9. COSTUME DESIGN, MINISERIES OR SPECIAL: ``Lonesome Dove,'' Part
Two, CBS.
   10. COSTUME DESIGN, VARIETY OR MUSIC PROGRAM: ``The Magic of
David Copperfield XI: The Explosive Encounter,'' CBS.
   11. SINGLE CAMERA PRODUCTION EDITING, SERIES: ``thirtysomething:
First Day, Last Day,'' ABC.
   12. SINGLE CAMERA PRODUCTION EDITING, MINISERIES OR SPECIAL:
``War and Remembrance,'' Part 10, ABC.
   13. MULTI-CAMERA PRODUCTION EDITING, SERIES: ``Murphy Brown:
Respect,'' CBS.
   14. MULTI-CAMERA PRODUCTION EDITING, MINISERIES OR SPECIAL:
``Great Performances: Dance in America: Gregory Hines Tap Dance in
America,'' PBS.
   15. GRAPHIC DESIGN AND TITLE SEQUENCES: No award given.
   16. HAIR STYLING FOR A SERIES: ``Quantum Leap: Double Identity,''
NBC.
   17. HAIR STYLING FOR A MINISERIES OR SPECIAL: ``Jack the
Ripper,'' Part One, CBS.
   18. LIGHTING DIRECTION FOR A COMEDY SERIES: ``Who's The Boss: A
Spirited Christmas,'' ABC.
   19. LIGHTING DIRECTION FOR A DRAMA SERIES, VARIETY SERIES,
MINISERIES OR SPECIAL: ``The Magic of David Copperfield XI: The
Explosive Encounter,'' CBS.
   20. MAKEUP FOR A MINISERIES OR SPECIAL: ``Lonesome Dove,'' Part
Four, CBS.
   21. MUSIC COMPOSITION FOR A SERIES: ``Falcon Crest: Dust to
Dust,'' CBS.
   22. MUSIC COMPOSITION FOR A MINISERIES OR SPECIAL: ``Lonesome
Dove,'' Part Four, CBS.
   23. MUSIC DIRECTION: ``Christmas in Washington,'' NBC.
   24. MUSIC AND LYRICS: ``Beauty and the Beast: A Distant Shore,''
CBS.
   25. MAIN TITLE THEME MUSIC: No award given.
   26. GUEST ACTOR IN A COMEDY SERIES: Cleavon Little, ``Dear
John,'' NBC.
   27. GUEST ACTOR IN A DRAMA SERIES: Joe Spano, ``Midnight
Caller,'' NBC.
   28. GUEST ACTRESS IN A COMEDY SERIES: Colleen Dewhurst, ``Murphy
Brown,'' CBS.
   29. GUEST ACTRESS IN A DRAMA SERIES: Kay Lenz, ``Midnight
Caller,'' NBC.
   30. SPECIAL EVENTS: ``Cirque de Soleil,'' HBO; ``The 11th Annual
Kennedy Center Honors: A Celebration of the Performing Arts,'' CBS;
``The 42nd Annual Tony Awards,'' CBS; ``The 17th Annual American
Film Institute Life Achievement Award: A Salute to Gregory Peck,''
NBC.
   31. CLASSICAL PROGRAM IN THE PERFORMING ARTS: ``Great
Performances: Bernstein at 70!,'' PBS.
   32. CHILDREN'S PROGRAM: ``Free to Be ... A Family,'' ABC.
   33. INFORMATIONAL SPECIAL: ``American Masters: Lillian Gish: The
Actor's Life for Me,'' ABC.
   34. INFORMATIONAL SERIES: ``Nature,'' PBS.
   35. ANIMATED PROGRAM (FOR PROGRAMMING ONE HOUR OR LESS):
``Garfield: Babes and Bullets,'' CBS.
   36. ANIMATED PROGRAM OF MORE THAN ONE HOUR: No award given.
   37. SOUND EDITING, SERIES: ``Star Trek: The Next Generation: Q
Who,'' syndicated.
   38. SOUND EDITING, MINISERIES OR SPECIAL: ``Lonesome Dove,'' Part
Three, CBS.
   39. SOUND MIXING, COMEDY, SERIES OR SPECIAL: ``Night Court: The
Last Temptation of Mac,'' NBC.
   40. SOUND MIXING, VARIETY OR MUSIC SERIES OR SPECIAL: ``Kenny,
Dolly and Willie: Something Inside So Strong,'' NBC.
   41. SOUND MIXING, DRAMA SERIES: ``Star Trek: The Next Generation:
Q Who,'' syndicated.
   42. SOUND MIXING, DRAMA MINISERIES OR SPECIAL: ``Lonesome Dove,''
Part Four, CBS.
   43. SPECIAL VISUAL EFFECTS: ``War and Remembrance,'' ABC.
   44. CAMERA-VIDEO TECHNICAL DIRECTION, SERIES: ``Night Court: Yet
Another Day in the Life,'' NBC.
   45. CAMERA-VIDEO TECHNICAL DIRECTION, MINISERIES OR SPECIAL:
``American Playhouse: The Meeting,'' PBS.
   46. CLASSICAL MUSIC-DANCE PROGRAMMING DIRECTING: No award given.
   47. CLASSICAL MUSIC-DANCE PROGRAMMING PERFORMANCE: ``Great
Performances: Dance in America: Baryshnikov Dances Balanchine,'' PBS.
   48. INFORMATIONAL PROGRAMMING DIRECTING: No award given.
   49. INFORMATIONAL PROGRAMMING PERFORMANCE: Hal Holbrook,
``Portrait of America: Alaska,'' TBS.
   50. INFORMATIONAL PROGRAMMING WRITING: John Heminway, ``The Mind:
Search for Mind,'' PBS.
   51. SPECIAL EVENTS DIRECTING: Dwight Hemion, ``The 11th Annual
Kennedy Center Honors: A Celebration of the Performing Arts,'' CBS.
   52. SPECIAL EVENTS LIGHTING DIRECTION: No award given.
   53. SPECIAL EVENTS MUSIC: No award given.
   54. SPECIAL EVENTS PERFORMANCE: Billy Crystal, ``The 31st Annual
Grammy Awards,'' CBS.
   55. SPECIAL EVENTS SOUND MIXING: ``The 31st Annual Grammy
Awards,'' CBS.
   56. SPECIAL EVENTS WRITING: Jeffrey Lane, ``The 42nd Annual Tony
Awards,'' CBS.
   57. CASTING, MINISERIES OR SPECIAL: ``Lonesome Dove,'' CBS.
