<FIRST>r a AM-GangViolence     09-17 0194</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Gang Violence,0201</SECOND>
<HEAD>Weekend Gang Violence Claims At Least Three Lives</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Police arrested 202 people early Sunday in an
attack on gang-related activity over the weekend that left at least
three people dead, including a 4-year-old boy.
   At least 72 people were arrested on felony charges involving
narcotics and other violations, said police detective Don Singer.
   Seven firearms and small quantities of cocaine, marijuana and a
hallucinogenic drug PCP were confiscated, Singer said.
   Despite the sweep, gang-related violence claimed at least three
lives and left 13 people wounded.
   In Garden Grove, south of Los Angeles, Frank Fernandez Jr., 4,
and Miguel Lorenzo Navarro, 18, were killed in a hail of gunfire
from a passing truck on Saturday, Police Lt. Ron Weigand said.
   Police believe one of the weapons used was a fully automatic
assault weapon and that Navarro was the target of the attack,
Weigand said.
   Elsewhere, an 18-year-old woman was killed when a gunman broke
into her Lennox apartment Saturday, officials said.
   Renee Johnson was shot and killed when a gang member kicked in
the door shortly after 3 a.m. and opened fire, sheriff's Detective
Harold Hladky said.
