<FIRST>r a AM-BusOverturns     09-17 0231</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Bus Overturns,0236</SECOND>
<HEAD>Bus Accident Injures 23 West German Tourists</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LANCASTER, N.Y. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A bus carrying West German tourists
spending a week in the United States skidded off a highway on Sunday
and overturned, injuring 23 people, police said.
   There were no serious injuries among the 24 passengers on the
Bluebird Coach Lines bus, which apparently slid on wet pavement on
the New York State Thruway and rolled onto its side, said State
Police Lt. Timothy Howard.
   Howard said speed and a roadway made slick by two days of rain
contributed to the accident, but said police aren't sure what caused
the accident.
   Rescuers from the Bowmansville Fire Department said about half of
the passengers had already walked off the bus, but the rest had to
be freed by way of a 6-by-4-foot hole that rescue personnel cut
through the bus roof.
   The passengers from Wurzburg, West Germany, arrived in Toronto on
Friday night to begin their trip to Rochester, Wurzburg's sister
city in the United States, according to Rochester sister cities
program coordinator Otto Fuchs.
   Fuchs said the group visited Niagara Falls on Saturday and was
headed to Rochester when the accident occurred Sunday morning. The
group was also scheduled to make trips to Philadelphia, Washington,
D.C., and New York City before returning home Friday.
   Police did not know if the driver was among the injured, Howard
said.
</TEXT>
